{% block content %}
<article class="dol-wrap">

  <p class="dol-num">Anishinaabemowin project · The talking doll</p>
  <h1>A doll that speaks Anishinaabemowin</h1>
  <p class="dol-lede">Part of the Anishinaabemowin project. Updated as the build progresses.</p>
  <p class="dol-updated">Last updated: June 12, 2026.</p>

  <figure class="dol-figure">
    <picture>
      <source srcset="/images/doll/doll-hero.webp" type="image/webp">
      <img src="/images/doll/doll-hero.jpg" alt="Concept render of a handmade soft doll on a wooden kitchen table in warm morning light." loading="lazy">
    </picture>
    <figcaption>Concept render (AI-generated). The real doll will be made in community.</figcaption>
  </figure>

  <div class="dol-col" style="margin-top: var(--gap-6)">
    <p>The idea arrived twice on the same day. In a community thread about the future of our language, a commenter suggested recording fluent speakers and putting their voices into a learning doll, a toy that teaches Anishinaabemowin alongside English, with the recordings kept by the Nations themselves. We had been carrying the same idea. When two people who have never met describe the same object, you build it.</p>
    <p>This page is the doll's public home, from idea to a child holding one.</p>
  </div>

  <section class="dol-sec" id="what">
    <div class="dol-sec__head"><span class="dol-num">01</span><h2>What it is</h2></div>
    <div class="dol-col">
      <p>A soft doll, sewn in community, with a fluent Elder's voice inside. Squeeze a hand and it speaks Anishinaabemowin. Squeeze again and it says the same thing in English. No screen. No app. No internet. Nothing leaves the doll, because nothing connects to anything. The recordings are made with consent, kept by the community, and placed into the doll the way a grandmother's voice belongs in a child's room: plainly, warmly, and on the family's terms.</p>
      <p>Why a doll, when there are already apps? Because the youngest learners, the ones who matter most for the next hundred years, do not read and should not be handed screens. A doll meets a two-year-old where she already lives. English gets thousands of hours into our children through devices before they ever hear ten minutes of Anishinaabemowin. The doll is ten minutes back.</p>
    </div>
  </section>

  <section class="dol-sec" id="plan">
    <div class="dol-sec__head"><span class="dol-num">02</span><h2>The plan, start to finish</h2></div>
    <ol class="dol-journey">
      <li class="dol-step">
        <div class="dol-step__n">1</div>
        <div class="dol-step__main">
          <div class="dol-step__head"><h3>Consent first.</h3> <span class="dol-chip dol-chip--inprogress">in progress</span></div>
          <p>A written consent record with the Elder that covers this exact use: his voice, in a toy, in children's homes. Not a blanket form. This is being designed now and nothing records until it is signed.</p>
        </div>
      </li>
      <li class="dol-step">
        <div class="dol-step__n">2</div>
        <div class="dol-step__main">
          <div class="dol-step__head"><h3>Choose the first phrases.</h3> <span class="dol-chip dol-chip--next">next</span></div>
          <p>A small set from the existing teaching collection: greetings, kitchen words, kindnesses, the things a doll would say. The Elder approves the list.</p>
        </div>
      </li>
      <li class="dol-step">
        <div class="dol-step__n">3</div>
        <div class="dol-step__main">
          <div class="dol-step__head"><h3>Pilot doll.</h3> <span class="dol-chip dol-chip--planned">planned</span></div>
          <p>One doll, sewn by hands in community, with a simple recordable sound module inside. Cheap, fast, real. Shown first to the Elder, then at a story night.</p>
        </div>
      </li>
      <li class="dol-step">
        <div class="dol-step__n">4</div>
        <div class="dol-step__main">
          <div class="dol-step__head"><h3>Family testing.</h3> <span class="dol-chip dol-chip--planned">planned</span></div>
          <p>A few homes, a few months. Does the squeeze placement make sense? Is the volume right? What do kids actually press?</p>
        </div>
      </li>
      <li class="dol-step">
        <div class="dol-step__n">5</div>
        <div class="dol-step__main">
          <div class="dol-step__head"><h3>The real build.</h3> <span class="dol-chip dol-chip--planned">planned</span></div>
          <p>A small electronics board, bilingual press-twice mode, child-safe battery compartment, toy-safety testing. Built so any Nation can load their own language into the same doll.</p>
        </div>
      </li>
      <li class="dol-step">
        <div class="dol-step__n">6</div>
        <div class="dol-step__main">
          <div class="dol-step__head"><h3>Small batch, given not sold.</h3> <span class="dol-chip dol-chip--planned">planned</span></div>
          <p>First dolls go as gifts: baby showers, ceremonies, language families.</p>
        </div>
      </li>
    </ol>
  </section>

  <section class="dol-sec" id="deeper">
    <div class="dol-sec__head"><span class="dol-num">03</span><h2>How deep this goes</h2></div>
    <div class="dol-col">
      <p>The doll is simple on the outside because the system behind it does the hard work. Two companion pages carry the depth:</p>
    </div>
    <div class="dol-cards is-2">
      <div class="dol-card">
        <h3><a href="/anishinaabemowin/doll/build">The build</a></h3>
        <p>Electronics, parts list, costs, safety, and how to make one.</p>
        <a class="dol-more" href="/anishinaabemowin/doll/build">Read the build &rarr;</a>
      </div>
      <div class="dol-card">
        <h3><a href="/anishinaabemowin/doll/process">The process</a></h3>
        <p>How a voice travels from an Elder's kitchen table into a doll, with consent checked at every step, and where Waaseyaa and Minoo fit.</p>
        <a class="dol-more" href="/anishinaabemowin/doll/process">Read the process &rarr;</a>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <section class="dol-sec" id="take-part">
    <div class="dol-sec__head"><span class="dol-num">04</span><h2>Take part</h2></div>
    <div class="dol-cta">
      <p>Sewers and beaders who want to make doll bodies. Fluent speakers who want their voice in a child's hands. Parents willing to test a pilot doll. Anyone with toy-safety or electronics experience.</p>
      <a class="dol-cta__btn" href="mailto:jonesrussell42@gmail.com">Email Russell &rarr;</a>
      <span class="dol-cta__addr">Write to Russell: <a href="mailto:jonesrussell42@gmail.com">jonesrussell42@gmail.com</a></span>
    </div>
  </section>

  <p class="dol-byline">Russell Jones, on behalf of OIATC. The idea belongs to the community thread that raised it. Corrections welcome.</p>

</article>
{% endblock %}

